### 3. Slide Decks Built for HeyGen Recording

Three PPTX files — one per course. Each lesson has a divider slide so Lauren knows exactly where she is in HeyGen. Speaker notes = the spoken script Lauren reads.

**Files in Claude outputs:**
- `lcai-course1-slides.pptx` — 23 slides, 5 lessons
- `lcai-course2-slides.pptx` — 28 slides, 6 lessons
- `lcai-course3-slides.pptx` — 26 slides, 5 lessons

**Design:** Dark theme (matches platform), cyan/violet/gold accent system, Arial Black headings, Trebuchet MS body. Course 1 = cyan accent, Course 2 = violet accent, Course 3 = gold accent.

**Recording workflow:**
1. Upload each deck to HeyGen
2. Record lesson by lesson using speaker notes as script (read the notes, not the slides)
3. Upload finished videos to Vimeo
4. Send embed URLs back to Claude — one URL per lesson
5. Claude will drop them into courses.html videoUrl fields

**Lesson URL placement in code — videoUrl fields:**
- Course 1: lessons l1-l5 (l6 is quiz, no video)
- Course 2: lessons l1-l6 (l7 is quiz, no video)
- Course 3: lessons l1-l5 (l6 is quiz, l7 is practice tasks — no video)
- Total: 16 video lessons to record

