## TECHNICAL NOTES FOR NEXT CLAUDE

- courses.html is a single-file HTML app — all CSS, HTML, JS in one file
- Course content is hardcoded in the `courses` JS array — admin builder is demo-only
- When editing: always download from outputs, edit programmatically with Python str.replace, re-upload
- Never copy-paste large code blocks — apostrophes in single-quoted strings will break the parser
- The `practiceTasks` array must stay in sync with what's in Supabase task_submissions
- `formatLeaderboardName()` handles "First L." display — admin Students tab shows full name
- `isImpersonating` flag must be checked before any Supabase writes (already done in submitTask)
- Video URLs go in each lesson's `videoUrl: ''` field — HeyGen/Vimeo URLs work via getEmbedHTML()
